Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Trim the @aubergine{1} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips then chop widthways into roughly 2cm pieces. Pop the aubergine chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and sprinkle over the @North Indian style spice mix{1}. Toss to coat, then arrange in a single layer. Roast the aubergine until golden brown and soft, ~{25-30%minutes} turning halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} over medium high heat. Once hot, add the onion and cook, stirring, until softened and turning brown, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the @korma curry paste{50%g} and cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}. Add the @tomato passata{1}, @red split lentils{100%g}, @water{350%ml}, @vegetable stock powder{1}, @sugar{½} (see ingredients for amount). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and bring to a boil. Once boiling, lower the heat to medium and cook until the lentils are soft, ~{20-25%minutes}. Stir regularly to make sure it doesn't stick to the bottom of the pan and add a splash of water if it is starting to get too thick.

Meanwhile, pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a saucepan and bring to the boil. When boiling, add @salt{0.25%tsp}, stir in the @basmati rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Once the lentils are cooked, add the @baby spinach{100%g} a handful at a time, stirring, until wilted and piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir through half the roasted aubergine, half the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g} and half the coriander. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once everything is ready, divide the rice between plates. Top with the dal, add the remaining roasted aubergine and remaining yoghurt. Scatter over the remaining coriander and enjoy!